/Question : At the seventh Sprint Review, The Stakeholder are disappointed and angry. They have determined that the product or system being built will not meet their need and will cost more than they are willing to spend. What factors likely led to this? 
/A) The Product Owner has not been keeping the stakeholders aware of the progress of the project
/B) The Stakeholders were not allowed to prioritize Product Backlog Items
/C) The Stakeholders have not been using the Sprint Reviews to inspect and evaluate progress
/D) The Project management office (PMO) has not been engaged adequately

A C